Players go on a fun yet dangerous journey in the enchanted realm of Poor Bunny, leading a lovable bunny through a maze of dangers so it may eat delicious carrots. The game is a classic skill test that enthralls with its straightforward idea: guide the rabbit through a dangerously cluttered obstacle course.

The vivid, bright platforms in Poor Bunny provide a striking visual contrast to the numerous lethal traps strewn throughout. Players need to have quick reactions and strategic vision to avoid these traps since they get faster and more complicated. The thrill of avoiding these dangers is enhanced by the pursuit of carrots, the game's money, which raises your score and unlocks a variety of more than a hundred oddball bunny characters, each with a distinct charm.

In the game, the golden carrot is an uncommon prize that irregularly appears and pays off handsomely. Capturing this elusive treasure, which is worth the equivalent of five regular carrots, is essential for players who want to quickly unlock new characters and increase their score.
